Hi, Team

=20

You said that you will not provide Proxy API in the future,

I wonder if I can do all the actions currently managed through VPM when =
using Proxy through REST API.

For example, is it possible to do detailed settings and Enable/Disable =
for the 100th Rule through API? I wonder if all management is possible =
through REST API even without using VPM.

=20

Additionally, you said that you can extract the policy into Excel.=20

Please tell me how to do that and also answer the question about whether =
it is impossible to insert the policy into Excel.

=20

Regards,

=20

=20



=20

=20

=20

From: broadcomsupport@apaccms.westcon.com =
[mailto:broadcomsupport@apaccms.westcon.com]=20
Sent: Thursday, April 17, 2025 4:00 PM
To: dsp0701@etechsystem.co.kr; kevin@etechsystem.co.kr
Cc: symantec-blue@etechsystem.co.kr; broadcomsupport.apac@westcon.com
Subject: {Case#80026785} ##High - P2 - SAMSUNG ELECTRONICS CO,.LTD-Is =
management via API possible in WEB VPM?

=20

Hi Team,

For the question below:

QQ2) I have another question. You said that you can create new objects, =
change policy contents, etc. through MC,2) I have another question. You =
said that you can create new objects, change policy contents, etc. =
through MC,
but is it possible to operate it with only the currently provided REST =
API as in VPM? Please answer with this focus.

REST API are only working on Management Center, you can create script to =
make management center to create policy/object and push the policy =
install to the proxy device.  It does not directly interact with VPM in =
proxy.


Regards,
Fauzee

  _____ =20

