Hi, Team

Thank you for your support.

I was thinking the same thing about the contents, but I opened a case =
because of the customer's request. For now, I understand that both are =
impossible.
Q1) Are there any plans to support these in the future?
Q2) Aren't only simple tasks such as creating and modifying objects =
possible through REST API in MC? Can all the functions provided by VPM =
be managed through REST API?

Regards,

=20

=20



=20

=20

=20

From: broadcomsupport@apaccms.westcon.com =
[mailto:broadcomsupport@apaccms.westcon.com]=20
Sent: Monday, April 14, 2025 3:58 PM
To: kevin@etechsystem.co.kr
Cc: symantec-blue@etechsystem.co.kr
Subject: {Case#80026785} ##High - P2 - SAMSUNG ELECTRONICS CO,.LTD-Is =
management via API possible in WEB VPM?

=20

Hi Jinyoung Hong,

Regarding your question please refer below for the answer:

Q1) The existing Java VPM has changed to support WEB VPM.
Is it possible to manage via API in WEB VPM?

The ProxySG does not have APIs that fetch data from the ProxySG or =
integrate with third-party products.

Workaround :=20

1. Use the Management Center REST API.


Management Center can connect to the ProxySG to apply changes.=20

See the documentation on the REST API: Management Center REST API =
<https://techdocs.broadcom.com/us/en/symantec-security-software/web-and-n=
etwork-security/management-center/3-3/api.html>=20

=20

2. The ProxySG has a number of read-only advanced URL like =
https://<ProxySG_IP_address>:8082/sysinfo or =
https://<ProxySG_IP_address>:8082/policy/=20

These are not APIs but the URLs can be used to fetch information about =
the proxy.=20

=20

3. The ProxySG's SSH interface can be utilized to make changes in the =
proxy configuration using the CLI. Using SSH it is possible to script =
commands for automation.=20

Refer to the CLI documentation: ProxySG Command Line Reference =
<https://techdocs.broadcom.com/us/en/symantec-security-software/web-and-n=
etwork-security/edge-swg/7-3/index2/_privileged.html>=20

ProxySG API to gather data and integrate with other reporting products =
<https://knowledge.broadcom.com/external/article/206621/proxysg-api-to-ga=
ther-data-and-integrate.html>=20

Q2) Can't the policy be reflected in Excel format instead of XML format =
in WEB VPM?

Currently ProxySG do not support the option to export policy to excel =
format. If you noticed before, in the policy trace, the policy is =
structured as a line of command which is check one by one with MISS and =
MATCH status. As ProxySG are built to use multiple layer like =
forwarding, authentication and access with different format and =
function, it almost impossible to create a general rule which can fit =
into Excel row and column.=20

Regards,
Fauzee








