style=3D'font-size:10.5pt;font-family:"Poppins",serif;background:white'>Q=
1) The existing Java VPM has changed to support WEB =
VPM.</span></strong><span lang=3DEN-US =
style=3D'font-size:10.5pt;font-family:"Poppins",serif'><br><strong><span =
style=3D'font-family:"Poppins",serif;background:white'>Is it possible to =
manage via API in WEB VPM?</span></strong></span><span =
lang=3DEN-US><o:p></o:p></span></p><p><span lang=3DEN-US>The ProxySG =
does not have APIs that fetch data from the ProxySG or integrate with =
third-party products.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p><span =
lang=3DEN-US>Workaround :&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p><p><span =
lang=3DEN-US>1. Use the Management Center REST =
API.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p><span lang=3DEN-US><br>Management Center =
can connect to the ProxySG to apply =
changes.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p><p><span lang=3DEN-US>See the =
documentation on the REST API:&nbsp;<a =
href=3D"https://techdocs.broadcom.com/us/en/symantec-security-software/we=
b-and-network-security/management-center/3-3/api.html" =
title=3D"Management Center REST API">Management Center REST =
API</a><o:p></o:p></span></p><p><span =
lang=3DEN-US>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p><p><span lang=3DEN-US>2. The =
ProxySG has a number of read-only advanced URL like =
https://&lt;ProxySG_IP_address&gt;:8082/sysinfo or =
https://&lt;ProxySG_IP_address&gt;:8082/policy/&nbsp;<br><br>These are =
not APIs but the URLs can be used to fetch information about the =
proxy.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p><p><span =
lang=3DEN-US>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p><p><span lang=3DEN-US>3. The =
ProxySG's SSH interface can be utilized to make changes in the proxy =
configuration using the CLI. Using SSH it is possible to script commands =
for automation.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p><p><span lang=3DEN-US>Refer =
to the CLI documentation:&nbsp;<a =
href=3D"https://techdocs.broadcom.com/us/en/symantec-security-software/we=
b-and-network-security/edge-swg/7-3/index2/_privileged.html">ProxySG =
Command Line Reference</a><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=3DMsoNormal =
style=3D'mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto'><span =
lang=3DEN-US><a =
href=3D"https://knowledge.broadcom.com/external/article/206621/proxysg-ap=
i-to-gather-data-and-integrate.html">ProxySG API to gather data and =
integrate with other reporting products</a><br><br></span><strong><span =
lang=3DEN-US =
style=3D'font-size:10.5pt;font-family:"Poppins",serif;background:white'>Q=
2) Can't the policy be reflected in Excel format instead of XML format =
in WEB VPM?</span></strong><b><span lang=3DEN-US =
style=3D'font-size:10.5pt;font-family:"Poppins",serif;background:white'><=
br><br></span></b><span lang=3DEN-US>Currently ProxySG do not support =
the option to export policy to excel format. If you noticed before, in =
the policy trace, the policy is structured as a line of command which is =
check one by one with MISS and MATCH status. As ProxySG are built to use =
multiple layer like forwarding, authentication and access with different =
format and function, it almost impossible to create a general rule which =
can fit into Excel row and =
column.&nbsp;<br><br>Regards,<br>Fauzee<o:p></o:p></span></p></div><p =
